FBIS4-24513 "drchi104_v_94026" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 31 May 1994 TAIWAN Export Zone Manufacturers Optimistic About Outlook Export Zone Manufacturers Optimistic About Outlook OW3105071994 Taipei CNA in English 0650 GMT 31 May 94 OW3105071994 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Danielle Yang] [Text] Taipei, May 31 (CNA) -- Most export processing zone (EPZ) manufacturers are optimistic about the export outlook in the second quarter of 1994, according to a survey conducted by the EPZ administration recently. A total of 91 manufacturers in the EPZ, or 50 percent of those surveyed, said they thought exports will remain stable in the second quarter. This is up from 46 percent from a similar survey in the first quarter. Fifty-nine manufacturers, or 33 percent, said they thought exports would take a turn for the better, higher than the 23 percent in the first quarter. However, 31 manufacturers, or 17 percent, thought exports would become worse. This is down from 31 percent in the previous quarter. EPZ officials said this [words indistinct] on rising [words indistinct] processing zones in Kaohsiung and Taichung.
